👤 Profile

Recommended Firestore Structure
1. users

Stores citizen information.

users
 └── userId
      ├── idNumber
      ├── fullName
      ├── email
      ├── phone
      ├── province
      └── createdAt
2. driversLicenses

Stores driver's license information.

driversLicenses
 └── licenseId
      ├── userId
      ├── licenseNumber
      ├── issueDate
      ├── expiryDate
      ├── status
      └── qrCode
3. vehicles

Stores vehicle information.

vehicles
 └── vehicleId
      ├── ownerId
      ├── registrationNumber
      ├── make
      ├── model
      ├── year
      └── diskExpiry
4. fines

Stores speeding tickets and penalties.

fines
 └── fineId
      ├── userId
      ├── vehicleId
      ├── amount
      ├── offense
      ├── status
      └── issuedDate
5. appointments

Bookings made by users.

appointments
 └── appointmentId
      ├── userId
      ├── serviceType
      ├── branch
      ├── date
      ├── time
      └── status
6. payments

Payment records.

payments
 └── paymentId
      ├── userId
      ├── amount
      ├── paymentType
      ├── status
      └── paidAt
7. notifications

Push notifications and alerts.

notifications
 └── notificationId
      ├── userId
      ├── title
      ├── message
      ├── read
      └── createdAt
8. branches

Traffic department branches.

branches
 └── branchId
      ├── name
      ├── address
      ├── province
      ├── phone
      └── operatingHours
9. roadAlerts

Road closures and traffic alerts.

roadAlerts
 └── alertId
      ├── title
      ├── location
      ├── severity
      ├── description
      └── createdAt
10. news

Traffic department announcements.

news
 └── newsId
      ├── title
      ├── content
      ├── image
      └── publishedAt
Optional Collections

If your lecturer wants something more advanced:

11. learnerTests
learnerTests
 └── testId

Stores practice questions.

12. supportChats
supportChats
 └── chatId

Stores chatbot conversations.

What Happens During Login?

The flow would be:

User enters ID Number
       ↓
Firebase Authentication
       ↓
Find user document
       ↓
Get userId
       ↓
Fetch:

users
driversLicenses
vehicles
fines
appointments
notifications

       ↓
Display on Home Screen

For a final-year project, I'd build 10 core collections:

users
driversLicenses
vehicles
fines
appointments
payments
notifications
branches
roadAlerts
news

These are enough to cover almost every feature you listed while keeping the database manageable and professional.